{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01E7TrWMTrKzccsdWQwN3EHf","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<project xmlns=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0\"\n     2→         xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n     3→         xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 https://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd\">\n     4→  <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>\n     5→  <artifactId>orders-service</artifactId>\n     6→  <packaging>war</packaging>\n     7→  <parent>\n     8→    <groupId>com.coffeeshop</groupId>\n     9→    <artifactId>coffeeshop-jakarta-liberty</artifactId>\n    10→    <version>0.2.0-SNAPSHOT</version>\n    11→    <!-- relativePath points to the root pom.xml (adjust if module is deeper) -->\n    12→    <relativePath>../pom.xml</relativePath>\n    13→  </parent>\n    14→  <properties>\n    15→    <maven.compiler.source>17</maven.compiler.source>\n    16→    <maven.compiler.target>17</maven.compiler.target>\n    17→    <project.build.sourceEncoding>UTF-8</project.build.sourceEncoding>\n    18→  </properties>\n    19→\n    20→  <dependencies>\n    21→    <dependency>\n    22→      <groupId>jakarta.platform</groupId>\n    23→      <artifactId>jakarta.jakartaee-web-api</artifactId>\n    24→      <version>${jakartaee.api.version}</version>\n    25→      <scope>provided</scope>\n    26→    </dependency>\n    27→\n    28→ \n    29→\n    30→    <dependency>\n    31→      <groupId>org.apache.kafka</groupId>\n    32→      <artifactId>kafka-clients</artifactId>\n    33→      <version>${kafka.clients.version}</version>\n    34→      <exclusions>\n    35→        <exclusion>\n    36→          <groupId>org.lz4</groupId>\n    37→          <artifactId>lz4-java</artifactId>\n    38→        </exclusion>\n    39→      </exclusions>\n    40→    </dependency>\n    41→    <dependency>\n    42→      <groupId>org.postgresql</groupId>\n    43→      <artifactId>postgresql</artifactId>\n    44→      <version>${postgresql.version}</version>\n    45→    </dependency>\n    46→       <!-- MicroProfile BOM imported at root; declare APIs explicitly for compilation -->\n    47→    <dependency>\n    48→      <groupId>org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging</groupId>\n    49→      <artifactId>microprofile-reactive-messaging-api</artifactId>\n    50→      <version>${mp.reactive.messaging.api.version}</version>\n    51→      <scope>provided</scope>\n    52→    </dependency>\n    53→    <dependency>\n    54→      <groupId>org.eclipse.microprofile.health</groupId>\n    55→      <artifactId>microprofile-health-api</artifactId>\n    56→      <version>${mp.health.api.version}</version>\n    57→      <scope>provided</scope>\n    58→    </dependency>\n    59→    <dependency>\n    60→      <groupId>com.coffeeshop</groupId>\n    61→      <artifactId>common</artifactId>\n    62→      <version>${project.version}</version>\n    63→    </dependency>\n    64→\n    65→  </dependencies>\n    66→\n    67→  <build>\n    68→    <finalName>orders-service</finalName>\n    69→    <resources>\n    70→      <resource>\n    71→        <directory>src/main/resources</directory>\n    72→        <filtering>false</filtering>\n    73→      </resource>\n    74→    </resources>\n    75→    <plugins>\n    76→      <plugin>\n    77→        <groupId>io.openliberty.tools</groupId>\n    78→        <artifactId>liberty-maven-plugin</artifactId>\n    79→      </plugin>\n    80→      <plugin>\n    81→        <artifactId>maven-war-plugin</artifactId>\n    82→        <version>3.4.0</version>\n    83→        <configuration>\n    84→          <failOnMissingWebXml>false</failOnMissingWebXml>\n    85→        </configuration>\n    86→      </plugin>\n    87→      <plugin>\n    88→  <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>\n    89→  <artifactId>maven-dependency-plugin</artifactId>\n    90→  <version>3.6.1</version>\n    91→  <executions>\n    92→    <execution>\n    93→      <id>copy-postgres-driver</id>\n    94→      <phase>process-resources</phase>\n    95→      <goals><goal>copy</goal></goals>\n    96→      <configuration>\n    97→        <artifactItems>\n    98→          <artifactItem>\n    99→            <groupId>org.postgresql</groupId>\n   100→            <artifactId>postgresql</artifactId>\n   101→            <version>${postgresql.version}</version>\n   102→            <outputDirectory>${project.basedir}/src/main/liberty/config/lib/global</outputDirectory>\n   103→            <overWrite>true</overWrite>\n   104→          </artifactItem>\n   105→        </artifactItems>\n   106→      </configuration>\n   107→    </execution>\n   108→  </executions>\n   109→</plugin>\n   110→\n   111→    </plugins>\n   112→  </build>\n   113→</project>\n   114→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"81831016-76f1-4927-ae62-9ae98a85d55f"}
