{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Mu6mtpHRKiqJeexzPXGk1P","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.kitchen.health;\n     2→\n     3→import org.eclipse.microprofile.health.HealthCheck;\n     4→import org.eclipse.microprofile.health.HealthCheckResponse;\n     5→import org.eclipse.microprofile.health.Readiness;\n     6→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     7→\n     8→@Readiness\n     9→@ApplicationScoped\n    10→public class BasicHealth implements HealthCheck {\n    11→    @Override\n    12→    public HealthCheckResponse call() {\n    13→        return HealthCheckResponse.up(\"kitchen-service\");\n    14→    }\n    15→}\n    16→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"041efbe9-8e7e-4091-bf2d-7d69eeeab189"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0122xExN6HigLLbfGMDouYRP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.kitchen.messaging;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Incoming;\n     5→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Outgoing;\n     6→\n     7→import jakarta.json.Json;\n     8→import jakarta.json.JsonObject;\n     9→\n    10→import java.io.StringReader;\n    11→\n    12→@ApplicationScoped\n    13→public class KitchenConsumer {\n    14→\n    15→    @Incoming(\"kitchen\")          // channel that reads topic: kitchen-commands\n    16→    @Outgoing(\"order-updates\")    // channel that writes topic: order-updates\n    17→    public String cookFood(String orderJson) {\n    18→        System.out.println(\"[kitchen] received: \" + orderJson);\n    19→        // Parse the incoming order (so we can carry orderId across)\n    20→        JsonObject in = Json.createReader(new StringReader(orderJson)).readObject();\n    21→\n    22→        // If original event had orderId, propagate it\n    23→        JsonObject out = Json.createObjectBuilder()\n    24→                .add(\"status\", \"READY\")\n    25→                .add(\"from\", \"kitchen\")\n    26→                .add(\"orderId\", in.containsKey(\"orderId\") ? in.getJsonNumber(\"orderId\").longValue() : -1)\n    27→                .build();\n    28→\n    29→        // This returns a real JSON object string: {\"status\":\"READY\",\"from\":\"kitchen\",\"orderId\":...}\n    30→        return out.toString();\n    31→    }\n    32→}\n    33→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"2c2b8152-d622-4912-bab4-2f58e614c6e2"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RKRRQH1oe9QDVDabjoGfwV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<persistence xmlns=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/persistence\" version=\"3.0\">\n     3→  <persistence-unit name=\"ordersPU\" transaction-type=\"JTA\">\n     4→    <jta-data-source>jdbc/ordersDS</jta-data-source>\n     5→    <properties>\n     6→      <property name=\"jakarta.persistence.schema-generation.database.action\" value=\"none\"/>\n     7→      <property name=\"jakarta.persistence.validation.mode\" value=\"NONE\"/>\n     8→      <property name=\"eclipselink.logging.level\" value=\"FINE\"/>\n     9→    </properties>\n    10→  </persistence-unit>\n    11→</persistence>\n    12→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"772eb44a-1e85-48a4-b7f6-fa6385992401"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0173Qh3ct4kMwRs2HUN2d3Ss","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# bootstrap (keep env, add a fallback so dev works even if env var is missing)\n     2→mp.messaging.connector.liberty-kafka.bootstrap.servers=${KAFKA_BOOTSTRAP:localhost:9092}\n     3→\n     4→# --- outgoing (unchanged) ---\n     5→mp.messaging.outgoing.barista.connector=liberty-kafka\n     6→mp.messaging.outgoing.barista.topic=barista-commands\n     7→mp.messaging.outgoing.barista.key.serializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer\n     8→mp.messaging.outgoing.barista.value.serializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer\n     9→\n    10→mp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.connector=liberty-kafka\n    11→mp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.topic=kitchen-commands\n    12→mp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.key.serializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer\n    13→mp.messaging.outgoing.kitchen.value.serializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer\n    14→\n    15→# --- incoming updates (add group.id) ---\n    16→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.connector=liberty-kafka\n    17→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.topic=order-updates\n    18→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.key.deserializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringDeserializer\n    19→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.value.deserializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringDeserializer\n    20→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.group.id=orders-service\n    21→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.auto.offset.reset=latest\n    22→\n    23→# Don’t shut the stream down on an exception (dev only)\n    24→mp.messaging.incoming.order-updates.failure-strategy=ignore\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"c1f8558a-4a8c-435a-abe8-6c687b52fb81"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CXSiD2KgbLpTGTW3RTLmzK","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→\n     2→app.name=barista-service\n     3→# Broker\n     4→mp.messaging.connector.liberty-kafka.bootstrap.servers=${KAFKA_BOOTSTRAP}\n     5→\n     6→# --- incoming: barista commands ---\n     7→mp.messaging.incoming.barista.connector=liberty-kafka\n     8→mp.messaging.incoming.barista.topic=barista-commands\n     9→mp.messaging.incoming.barista.key.deserializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringDeserializer\n    10→mp.messaging.incoming.barista.value.deserializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringDeserializer\n    11→# nice for dev: start at latest or earliest depending on your preference\n    12→mp.messaging.incoming.barista.auto.offset.reset=latest\n    13→mp.messaging.incoming.barista.group.id=barista-service-dev\n    14→\n    15→# --- outgoing: updates -> order-updates topic ---\n    16→mp.messaging.outgoing.order-updates.connector=liberty-kafka\n    17→mp.messaging.outgoing.order-updates.topic=order-updates\n    18→mp.messaging.outgoing.order-updates.key.serializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer\n    19→mp.messaging.outgoing.order-updates.value.serializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer\n    20→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"37797fc5-86b7-4cbb-ba6d-cd8a563001ac"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Tgi7PrJkh1CwR7XWdzvUDJ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→mp.messaging.connector.liberty-kafka.bootstrap.servers=${KAFKA_BOOTSTRAP}\n     2→mp.messaging.incoming.kitchen.connector=liberty-kafka\n     3→mp.messaging.incoming.kitchen.topic=kitchen-commands\n     4→mp.messaging.incoming.kitchen.group.id=kitchen-service\n     5→mp.messaging.incoming.kitchen.key.deserializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringDeserializer\n     6→mp.messaging.incoming.kitchen.value.deserializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringDeserializer\n     7→mp.messaging.outgoing.order-updates.connector=liberty-kafka\n     8→mp.messaging.outgoing.order-updates.topic=order-updates\n     9→mp.messaging.outgoing.order-updates.key.serializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer\n    10→mp.messaging.outgoing.order-updates.value.serializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer\n    11→app.name=kitchen-service\n    12→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"15458580-9fc6-4561-a45f-109e88633dd7"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013PUdL32KrUw984Qfbp8FHo","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<server>\n     2→  <logging traceSpecification=\"JPA=all:com.ibm.ws.jpa.*=all\"/>\n     3→\n     4→  <featureManager>\n     5→    <feature>webProfile-10.0</feature>\n     6→\n     7→    <!-- JPA – BOTH are needed for @PersistenceContext -->\n     8→    <feature>persistence-3.1</feature>\n     9→    <feature>persistenceContainer-3.1</feature>\n    10→\n    11→    <!-- Validation is required because you use @Valid etc. -->\n    12→    <feature>beanValidation-3.0</feature>\n    13→\n    14→    <!-- your MP features -->\n    15→    <feature>mpConfig-3.1</feature>\n    16→    <feature>mpHealth-4.0</feature>\n    17→    <feature>mpOpenAPI-3.1</feature>\n    18→    <feature>mpMetrics-5.1</feature>\n    19→    <feature>mpRestClient-3.0</feature>\n    20→    <feature>mpReactiveMessaging-3.0</feature>\n    21→    <feature>mpJwt-2.1</feature>\n    22→  </featureManager>\n    23→\n    24→  <httpEndpoint id=\"defaultHttpEndpoint\" host=\"*\" httpPort=\"9080\" httpsPort=\"9443\"/>\n    25→\n    26→  <basicRegistry id=\"basic\" realm=\"defaultRealm\">\n    27→    <user name=\"admin\" password=\"adminpwd\"/>\n    28→  </basicRegistry>\n    29→\n    30→  <!-- JDBC driver jar lives in /config/lib/global inside the container -->\n    31→  <library id=\"jdbcLib\">\n    32→    <fileset dir=\"${server.config.dir}/lib/global\" includes=\"*.jar\"/>\n    33→  </library>\n    34→\n    35→  <dataSource id=\"ordersDS\" jndiName=\"jdbc/ordersDS\">\n    36→    <jdbcDriver libraryRef=\"jdbcLib\"/>\n    37→    <properties\n    38→      databaseName=\"${env.DB_NAME}\"\n    39→      user=\"${env.DB_USER}\"\n    40→      password=\"${env.DB_PASSWORD}\"\n    41→      serverName=\"${env.DB_HOST}\"\n    42→      portNumber=\"${env.DB_PORT}\"/>\n    43→  </dataSource>\n    44→\n    45→  <webApplication id=\"orders-ui\"\n    46→                location=\"${server.config.dir}/apps/orders-service.war\"\n    47→                contextRoot=\"/\"/>\n    48→\n    49→\n    50→</server>\n    51→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"265683cf-9bb4-4fe7-910b-b72dee13d7da"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LcuKSZtpJu7K9kT9A6HjSF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→-- Aligns with OrderEntity fields/status usage\n     2→CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS orders (\n     3→  id        BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n     4→  customer  VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,\n     5→  item      VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,\n     6→  quantity  INTEGER      NOT NULL CHECK (quantity > 0),\n     7→  status    VARCHAR(20)  NOT NULL,\n     8→  created   TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),\n     9→  updated   TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()\n    10→);\n    11→\n    12→CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_orders_status ON orders(status);\n    13→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"907ef906-4f60-4d05-9821-4e35a6e6ba76"}
