{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01DEp9TGe6wUS6hdKKyna3Ea","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me rewrite all the pom.xml files and Java code for Quarkus. The key decisions for the migration:\n\n1. **Quarkus 3.17.x** (latest stable, uses Jakarta EE namespace natively)\n2. **quarkus-resteasy-reactive-jackson** for REST endpoints\n3. **quarkus-hibernate-orm-panache** or plain **quarkus-hibernate-orm** + **quarkus-jdbc-h2** for DB (H2 in-memory for standalone testing without PostgreSQL)\n4. **quarkus-smallrye-reactive-messaging-kafka** for Kafka messaging\n5. **quarkus-smallrye-health** for health checks\n6. Since Jakarta imports (jakarta.ws.rs, jakarta.persistence, etc.) are already used and Quarkus 3.x uses Jakarta namespace, many imports stay the same\n7. Key changes: Remove Liberty-specific configs (server.xml, web.xml), replace with `application.properties`, remove `@ApplicationPath` classes (Quarkus handles this via config), replace JSON-B with Jackson\n\nFor the Docker container to work standalone without Kafka/Postgres, I'll configure:\n- H2 in-memory database as default\n- Graceful degradation for messaging (disabled when Kafka not available)\n\nLet me now write all the files:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":558,"cache_read_input_tokens":59613,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":558,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1309},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"d406926f-4957-42bd-8c70-7a248aac7b32"}
