{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_0159BHUA5yUuZarLXTVU6tAs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01PWWVruPQyuEii8v56MeqDs","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Refactor Java files for Quarkus","subagent_type":"general-purpose","prompt":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE / Open Liberty coffee shop application to Quarkus. I need you to write the refactored Java source files. The working directory is /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__coffee-shop__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output\n\nHere are ALL the files that need to be written/updated:\n\n## 1. common module - These files are OK as-is (jakarta.validation works in Quarkus):\n- common/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/common/domain/OrderRequest.java - KEEP AS IS\n- common/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/common/domain/OrderAck.java - KEEP AS IS\n- common/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/common/domain/OrderStatus.java - KEEP AS IS\n\n## 2. orders-service - Need to refactor for Quarkus\n\n### DELETE (Quarkus doesn't need JAX-RS Application classes):\n- orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/api/OrdersApplication.java - DELETE \n- orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/web/RestApp.java - DELETE\n- orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/api/OrdersResource.java - DELETE (there's a duplicate in web/)\n\n### REFACTOR orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/web/OrdersResource.java:\nCurrent content:\n```java\npackage com.coffeeshop.orders.web;\n\nimport com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderRequest;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.service.OrderService;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.validation.Valid;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.Consumes;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.POST;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.PathParam;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\nimport java.util.Map;\n\n@Path(\"/orders\")\n@Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n@Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\npublic class OrdersResource {\n  @Inject OrderService orderService;\n  @POST\n  public Response create(@Valid OrderRequest request) {\n    String id = orderService.place(request);\n    return Response.accepted(Map.of(\"id\", id)).build();\n  }\n  @GET @Path(\"/{id}\")\n  public Response get(@PathParam(\"id\") long id) {\n    return Response.ok(Map.of(\"id\", id)).build();\n  }\n}\n```\n\nRefactored - use the OrderRepository to actually retrieve the entity in the GET method:\n```java\npackage com.coffeeshop.orders.web;\n\nimport com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderRequest;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderEntity;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderRepository;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.service.OrderService;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.validation.Valid;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.*;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\nimport java.util.Map;\n\n@Path(\"/orders\")\n@Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n@Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\npublic class OrdersResource {\n    @Inject\n    OrderService orderService;\n\n    @Inject\n    OrderRepository repo;\n\n    @POST\n    public Response create(@Valid OrderRequest request) {\n        String id = orderService.place(request);\n        return Response.accepted(Map.of(\"id\", id)).build();\n    }\n\n    @GET\n    @Path(\"/{id}\")\n    public Response get(@PathParam(\"id\") long id) {\n        OrderEntity entity = repo.find(id);\n        if (entity == null) {\n            return Response.status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND).build();\n        }\n        return Response.ok(entity).build();\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### REFACTOR orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/domain/OrderRepository.java:\nReplace @PersistenceContext with @Inject, remove unitName:\n```java\npackage com.coffeeshop.orders.domain;\n\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\nimport jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class OrderRepository {\n\n    @Inject\n    EntityManager em;\n\n    @Transactional\n    public Long save(OrderEntity e) {\n        em.persist(e);\n        em.flush();\n        return e.getId();\n    }\n\n    public OrderEntity find(long id) {\n        return em.find(OrderEntity.class, id);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### KEEP orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/domain/OrderEntity.java - OK as-is (jakarta.persistence works in Quarkus)\n\n### REFACTOR orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/service/OrderService.java:\nKeep as-is but add @Transactional:\n```java\npackage com.coffeeshop.orders.service;\n\nimport com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderRequest;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderEntity;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderRepository;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.messaging.OrdersPipeline;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\nimport jakarta.validation.Valid;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class OrderService {\n    @Inject\n    OrderRepository repo;\n\n    @Inject\n    OrdersPipeline pipeline;\n\n    @Transactional\n    public String place(@Valid OrderRequest req) {\n        var e = new OrderEntity();\n        e.setCustomer(req.customer());\n        e.setItem(req.item());\n        e.setQuantity(req.quantity());\n        repo.save(e);\n\n        // simple routing: drinks -> barista, everything else -> kitchen\n        if (isDrink(req.item())) {\n            pipeline.publishToBarista(new OrdersPipeline.OrderCommand(\"BARISTA\", e.getId(), req.item(), req.quantity()));\n        } else {\n            pipeline.publishToKitchen(new OrdersPipeline.OrderCommand(\"KITCHEN\", e.getId(), req.item(), req.quantity()));\n        }\n        return String.valueOf(e.getId());\n    }\n\n    private boolean isDrink(String item) {\n        if (item == null) return false;\n        var s = item.toLowerCase();\n        return s.contains(\"coffee\") || s.contains(\"latte\") || s.contains(\"espresso\")\n            || s.contains(\"cappuccino\") || s.contains(\"americano\") || s.contains(\"mocha\")\n            || s.contains(\"tea\");\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### REFACTOR orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/messaging/OrdersPipeline.java:\nReplace JSON-B with Jackson (ObjectMapper):\n```java\npackage com.coffeeshop.orders.messaging;\n\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Channel;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Emitter;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class OrdersPipeline {\n\n    @Inject\n    @Channel(\"barista\")\n    Emitter<String> barista;\n\n    @Inject\n    @Channel(\"kitchen\")\n    Emitter<String> kitchen;\n\n    private static final ObjectMapper MAPPER = new ObjectMapper();\n\n    public void publishToBarista(OrderCommand cmd) {\n        try {\n            System.out.println(\"[orders] sending barista command: \" + cmd);\n            barista.send(MAPPER.writeValueAsString(cmd));\n        } catch (JsonProcessingException e) {\n            throw new RuntimeException(\"Failed to serialize barista command\", e);\n        }\n    }\n\n    public void publishToKitchen(OrderCommand cmd) {\n        try {\n            System.out.println(\"[orders] sending kitchen command: \" + cmd);\n            kitchen.send(MAPPER.writeValueAsString(cmd));\n        } catch (JsonProcessingException e) {\n            throw new RuntimeException(\"Failed to serialize kitchen command\", e);\n        }\n    }\n\n    // simple DTO for messages\n    public record OrderCommand(String target, long orderId, String item, int quantity) {}\n}\n```\n\n### REFACTOR orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/messaging/OrderUpdatesListener.java:\nReplace JSON-B with Jackson:\n```java\npackage com.coffeeshop.orders.messaging;\n\nimport com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderStatus;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderRepository;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Incoming;\n\nimport java.util.Locale;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class OrderUpdatesListener {\n\n    private static final ObjectMapper MAPPER = new ObjectMapper();\n\n    public static final class OrderUpdate {\n        public Long orderId;\n        public String status;\n        public String from;\n    }\n\n    @Inject\n    OrderRepository repo;\n\n    @Incoming(\"order-updates\")\n    @Transactional\n    public void apply(String payload) {\n        try {\n            if (payload == null) return;\n            String json = payload.trim();\n\n            // Unwrap if the payload is a *stringified* JSON object.\n            int safety = 3;\n            while (safety-- > 0\n                && json.length() >= 2\n                && json.charAt(0) == '\"'\n                && json.charAt(json.length() - 1) == '\"') {\n                json = MAPPER.readValue(json, String.class).trim();\n            }\n\n            OrderUpdate evt = MAPPER.readValue(json, OrderUpdate.class);\n            if (evt == null || evt.status == null || evt.orderId == null) {\n                System.err.println(\"[order-updates] ignored event: \" + json);\n                return;\n            }\n\n            var entity = repo.find(evt.orderId);\n            if (entity == null) return;\n            entity.setStatus(OrderStatus.valueOf(evt.status.toUpperCase(Locale.ROOT)));\n\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            System.err.println(\"[order-updates] parse/update error: \" + e + \" payload=\" + payload);\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### REFACTOR orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/health/BasicHealth.java:\nSame API (SmallRye implements MicroProfile Health):\n```java\npackage com.coffeeshop.orders.health;\n\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.health.HealthCheck;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.health.HealthCheckResponse;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.health.Readiness;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n\n@Readiness\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class BasicHealth implements HealthCheck {\n    @Override\n    public HealthCheckResponse call() {\n        return HealthCheckResponse.up(\"orders-service\");\n    }\n}\n```\n(This is identical - keep as-is)\n\n### KEEP orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/web/ConstraintViolationExceptionMapper.java - OK as-is\n\n## 3. barista-service - Need to refactor for Quarkus\n\n### DELETE:\n- barista-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/barista/api/BaristaApplication.java - DELETE\n\n### KEEP barista-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/barista/api/StatusResource.java - OK as-is\n### KEEP barista-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/barista/health/BasicHealth.java - OK as-is\n\n### REFACTOR barista-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/barista/messaging/BaristaConsumer.java:\nReplace JSON-B with Jackson:\n```java\npackage com.coffeeshop.barista.messaging;\n\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.core.type.TypeReference;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Incoming;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Outgoing;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Message;\n\nimport java.util.HashMap;\nimport java.util.Map;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class BaristaConsumer {\n\n    private final ObjectMapper mapper = new ObjectMapper();\n\n    @Incoming(\"barista\")\n    @Outgoing(\"order-updates\")\n    public Message<String> makeCoffee(String orderJson) {\n        try {\n            System.out.println(\"[barista] received: \" + orderJson);\n            Map<String, Object> in = mapper.readValue(orderJson, new TypeReference<Map<String, Object>>() {});\n\n            Object orderId = in.get(\"orderId\");\n\n            Map<String, Object> out = new HashMap<>();\n            if (orderId != null) {\n                out.put(\"orderId\", orderId);\n            }\n            out.put(\"status\", \"READY\");\n            out.put(\"from\", \"barista\");\n\n            return Message.of(mapper.writeValueAsString(out));\n\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            System.err.println(\"[barista] parse/update error: \" + e + \" payload=\" + orderJson);\n            throw new RuntimeException(e);\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## 4. kitchen-service - Need to refactor for Quarkus\n\n### DELETE:\n- kitchen-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/kitchen/api/KitchenApplication.java - DELETE\n\n### KEEP kitchen-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/kitchen/api/StatusResource.java - OK as-is\n### KEEP kitchen-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/kitchen/health/BasicHealth.java - OK as-is\n\n### REFACTOR kitchen-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/kitchen/messaging/KitchenConsumer.java:\nReplace javax.json with Jackson:\n```java\npackage com.coffeeshop.kitchen.messaging;\n\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.core.type.TypeReference;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Incoming;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Outgoing;\n\nimport java.util.HashMap;\nimport java.util.Map;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class KitchenConsumer {\n\n    private final ObjectMapper mapper = new ObjectMapper();\n\n    @Incoming(\"kitchen\")\n    @Outgoing(\"order-updates\")\n    public String cookFood(String orderJson) {\n        try {\n            System.out.println(\"[kitchen] received: \" + orderJson);\n            Map<String, Object> in = mapper.readValue(orderJson, new TypeReference<Map<String, Object>>() {});\n\n            Map<String, Object> out = new HashMap<>();\n            out.put(\"status\", \"READY\");\n            out.put(\"from\", \"kitchen\");\n            out.put(\"orderId\", in.containsKey(\"orderId\") ? in.get(\"orderId\") : -1);\n\n            return mapper.writeValueAsString(out);\n\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            System.err.println(\"[kitchen] parse/update error: \" + e + \" payload=\" + orderJson);\n            throw new RuntimeException(e);\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\nPlease write ALL the files listed above that need refactoring. For files marked DELETE, delete the file. For files marked KEEP, leave them as-is. For files marked REFACTOR, write the new content as specified.\n\nAlso write the following for the OrderRepository (note @Transactional should be on OrderService, not OrderRepository to avoid nested transactions; but we can keep @Transactional on save for direct usage):\n\nWrite each file using the Write tool. Delete files that need deleting using Bash (rm command)."}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6828,"cache_read_input_tokens":76352,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6828,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":4559},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"d6326b2e-6d5f-4aa0-b782-8906c7761e36"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE / Open Liberty coffee shop application to Quarkus. I need you to write the refactored Java source files. The working directory is /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__coffee-shop__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output\n\nHere are ALL the files that need to be written/updated:\n\n## 1. common module - These files are OK as-is (jakarta.validation works in Quarkus):\n- common/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/common/domain/OrderRequest.java - KEEP AS IS\n- common/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/common/domain/OrderAck.java - KEEP AS IS\n- common/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/common/domain/OrderStatus.java - KEEP AS IS\n\n## 2. orders-service - Need to refactor for Quarkus\n\n### DELETE (Quarkus doesn't need JAX-RS Application classes):\n- orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/api/OrdersApplication.java - DELETE \n- orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/web/RestApp.java - DELETE\n- orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/api/OrdersResource.java - DELETE (there's a duplicate in web/)\n\n### REFACTOR orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/web/OrdersResource.java:\nCurrent content:\n```java\npackage com.coffeeshop.orders.web;\n\nimport com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderRequest;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.service.OrderService;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.validation.Valid;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.Consumes;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.POST;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.PathParam;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\nimport java.util.Map;\n\n@Path(\"/orders\")\n@Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n@Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\npublic class OrdersResource {\n  @Inject OrderService orderService;\n  @POST\n  public Response create(@Valid OrderRequest request) {\n    String id = orderService.place(request);\n    return Response.accepted(Map.of(\"id\", id)).build();\n  }\n  @GET @Path(\"/{id}\")\n  public Response get(@PathParam(\"id\") long id) {\n    return Response.ok(Map.of(\"id\", id)).build();\n  }\n}\n```\n\nRefactored - use the OrderRepository to actually retrieve the entity in the GET method:\n```java\npackage com.coffeeshop.orders.web;\n\nimport com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderRequest;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderEntity;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderRepository;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.service.OrderService;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.validation.Valid;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.*;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\nimport java.util.Map;\n\n@Path(\"/orders\")\n@Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n@Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\npublic class OrdersResource {\n    @Inject\n    OrderService orderService;\n\n    @Inject\n    OrderRepository repo;\n\n    @POST\n    public Response create(@Valid OrderRequest request) {\n        String id = orderService.place(request);\n        return Response.accepted(Map.of(\"id\", id)).build();\n    }\n\n    @GET\n    @Path(\"/{id}\")\n    public Response get(@PathParam(\"id\") long id) {\n        OrderEntity entity = repo.find(id);\n        if (entity == null) {\n            return Response.status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND).build();\n        }\n        return Response.ok(entity).build();\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### REFACTOR orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/domain/OrderRepository.java:\nReplace @PersistenceContext with @Inject, remove unitName:\n```java\npackage com.coffeeshop.orders.domain;\n\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\nimport jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class OrderRepository {\n\n    @Inject\n    EntityManager em;\n\n    @Transactional\n    public Long save(OrderEntity e) {\n        em.persist(e);\n        em.flush();\n        return e.getId();\n    }\n\n    public OrderEntity find(long id) {\n        return em.find(OrderEntity.class, id);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### KEEP orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/domain/OrderEntity.java - OK as-is (jakarta.persistence works in Quarkus)\n\n### REFACTOR orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/service/OrderService.java:\nKeep as-is but add @Transactional:\n```java\npackage com.coffeeshop.orders.service;\n\nimport com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderRequest;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderEntity;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderRepository;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.messaging.OrdersPipeline;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\nimport jakarta.validation.Valid;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class OrderService {\n    @Inject\n    OrderRepository repo;\n\n    @Inject\n    OrdersPipeline pipeline;\n\n    @Transactional\n    public String place(@Valid OrderRequest req) {\n        var e = new OrderEntity();\n        e.setCustomer(req.customer());\n        e.setItem(req.item());\n        e.setQuantity(req.quantity());\n        repo.save(e);\n\n        // simple routing: drinks -> barista, everything else -> kitchen\n        if (isDrink(req.item())) {\n            pipeline.publishToBarista(new OrdersPipeline.OrderCommand(\"BARISTA\", e.getId(), req.item(), req.quantity()));\n        } else {\n            pipeline.publishToKitchen(new OrdersPipeline.OrderCommand(\"KITCHEN\", e.getId(), req.item(), req.quantity()));\n        }\n        return String.valueOf(e.getId());\n    }\n\n    private boolean isDrink(String item) {\n        if (item == null) return false;\n        var s = item.toLowerCase();\n        return s.contains(\"coffee\") || s.contains(\"latte\") || s.contains(\"espresso\")\n            || s.contains(\"cappuccino\") || s.contains(\"americano\") || s.contains(\"mocha\")\n            || s.contains(\"tea\");\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### REFACTOR orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/messaging/OrdersPipeline.java:\nReplace JSON-B with Jackson (ObjectMapper):\n```java\npackage com.coffeeshop.orders.messaging;\n\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Channel;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Emitter;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class OrdersPipeline {\n\n    @Inject\n    @Channel(\"barista\")\n    Emitter<String> barista;\n\n    @Inject\n    @Channel(\"kitchen\")\n    Emitter<String> kitchen;\n\n    private static final ObjectMapper MAPPER = new ObjectMapper();\n\n    public void publishToBarista(OrderCommand cmd) {\n        try {\n            System.out.println(\"[orders] sending barista command: \" + cmd);\n            barista.send(MAPPER.writeValueAsString(cmd));\n        } catch (JsonProcessingException e) {\n            throw new RuntimeException(\"Failed to serialize barista command\", e);\n        }\n    }\n\n    public void publishToKitchen(OrderCommand cmd) {\n        try {\n            System.out.println(\"[orders] sending kitchen command: \" + cmd);\n            kitchen.send(MAPPER.writeValueAsString(cmd));\n        } catch (JsonProcessingException e) {\n            throw new RuntimeException(\"Failed to serialize kitchen command\", e);\n        }\n    }\n\n    // simple DTO for messages\n    public record OrderCommand(String target, long orderId, String item, int quantity) {}\n}\n```\n\n### REFACTOR orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/messaging/OrderUpdatesListener.java:\nReplace JSON-B with Jackson:\n```java\npackage com.coffeeshop.orders.messaging;\n\nimport com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderStatus;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderRepository;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Incoming;\n\nimport java.util.Locale;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class OrderUpdatesListener {\n\n    private static final ObjectMapper MAPPER = new ObjectMapper();\n\n    public static final class OrderUpdate {\n        public Long orderId;\n        public String status;\n        public String from;\n    }\n\n    @Inject\n    OrderRepository repo;\n\n    @Incoming(\"order-updates\")\n    @Transactional\n    public void apply(String payload) {\n        try {\n            if (payload == null) return;\n            String json = payload.trim();\n\n            // Unwrap if the payload is a *stringified* JSON object.\n            int safety = 3;\n            while (safety-- > 0\n                && json.length() >= 2\n                && json.charAt(0) == '\"'\n                && json.charAt(json.length() - 1) == '\"') {\n                json = MAPPER.readValue(json, String.class).trim();\n            }\n\n            OrderUpdate evt = MAPPER.readValue(json, OrderUpdate.class);\n            if (evt == null || evt.status == null || evt.orderId == null) {\n                System.err.println(\"[order-updates] ignored event: \" + json);\n                return;\n            }\n\n            var entity = repo.find(evt.orderId);\n            if (entity == null) return;\n            entity.setStatus(OrderStatus.valueOf(evt.status.toUpperCase(Locale.ROOT)));\n\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            System.err.println(\"[order-updates] parse/update error: \" + e + \" payload=\" + payload);\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### REFACTOR orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/health/BasicHealth.java:\nSame API (SmallRye implements MicroProfile Health):\n```java\npackage com.coffeeshop.orders.health;\n\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.health.HealthCheck;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.health.HealthCheckResponse;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.health.Readiness;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n\n@Readiness\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class BasicHealth implements HealthCheck {\n    @Override\n    public HealthCheckResponse call() {\n        return HealthCheckResponse.up(\"orders-service\");\n    }\n}\n```\n(This is identical - keep as-is)\n\n### KEEP orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/web/ConstraintViolationExceptionMapper.java - OK as-is\n\n## 3. barista-service - Need to refactor for Quarkus\n\n### DELETE:\n- barista-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/barista/api/BaristaApplication.java - DELETE\n\n### KEEP barista-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/barista/api/StatusResource.java - OK as-is\n### KEEP barista-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/barista/health/BasicHealth.java - OK as-is\n\n### REFACTOR barista-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/barista/messaging/BaristaConsumer.java:\nReplace JSON-B with Jackson:\n```java\npackage com.coffeeshop.barista.messaging;\n\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.core.type.TypeReference;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Incoming;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Outgoing;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Message;\n\nimport java.util.HashMap;\nimport java.util.Map;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class BaristaConsumer {\n\n    private final ObjectMapper mapper = new ObjectMapper();\n\n    @Incoming(\"barista\")\n    @Outgoing(\"order-updates\")\n    public Message<String> makeCoffee(String orderJson) {\n        try {\n            System.out.println(\"[barista] received: \" + orderJson);\n            Map<String, Object> in = mapper.readValue(orderJson, new TypeReference<Map<String, Object>>() {});\n\n            Object orderId = in.get(\"orderId\");\n\n            Map<String, Object> out = new HashMap<>();\n            if (orderId != null) {\n                out.put(\"orderId\", orderId);\n            }\n            out.put(\"status\", \"READY\");\n            out.put(\"from\", \"barista\");\n\n            return Message.of(mapper.writeValueAsString(out));\n\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            System.err.println(\"[barista] parse/update error: \" + e + \" payload=\" + orderJson);\n            throw new RuntimeException(e);\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## 4. kitchen-service - Need to refactor for Quarkus\n\n### DELETE:\n- kitchen-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/kitchen/api/KitchenApplication.java - DELETE\n\n### KEEP kitchen-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/kitchen/api/StatusResource.java - OK as-is\n### KEEP kitchen-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/kitchen/health/BasicHealth.java - OK as-is\n\n### REFACTOR kitchen-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/kitchen/messaging/KitchenConsumer.java:\nReplace javax.json with Jackson:\n```java\npackage com.coffeeshop.kitchen.messaging;\n\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.core.type.TypeReference;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Incoming;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Outgoing;\n\nimport java.util.HashMap;\nimport java.util.Map;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class KitchenConsumer {\n\n    private final ObjectMapper mapper = new ObjectMapper();\n\n    @Incoming(\"kitchen\")\n    @Outgoing(\"order-updates\")\n    public String cookFood(String orderJson) {\n        try {\n            System.out.println(\"[kitchen] received: \" + orderJson);\n            Map<String, Object> in = mapper.readValue(orderJson, new TypeReference<Map<String, Object>>() {});\n\n            Map<String, Object> out = new HashMap<>();\n            out.put(\"status\", \"READY\");\n            out.put(\"from\", \"kitchen\");\n            out.put(\"orderId\", in.containsKey(\"orderId\") ? in.get(\"orderId\") : -1);\n\n            return mapper.writeValueAsString(out);\n\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            System.err.println(\"[kitchen] parse/update error: \" + e + \" payload=\" + orderJson);\n            throw new RuntimeException(e);\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\nPlease write ALL the files listed above that need refactoring. For files marked DELETE, delete the file. For files marked KEEP, leave them as-is. For files marked REFACTOR, write the new content as specified.\n\nAlso write the following for the OrderRepository (note @Transactional should be on OrderService, not OrderRepository to avoid nested transactions; but we can keep @Transactional on save for direct usage):\n\nWrite each file using the Write tool. Delete files that need deleting using Bash (rm command)."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PWWVruPQyuEii8v56MeqDs","session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"18fe69f4-fa0b-4198-aba6-66c133c48ef4"}
