{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CExNSSJPG6PNPRAUjnbeo7","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.orders.web;\n     2→\n     3→import com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderRequest;\n     4→import com.coffeeshop.orders.service.OrderService;\n     5→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     6→import jakarta.validation.Valid;\n     7→import jakarta.ws.rs.Consumes;\n     8→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.POST;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.PathParam;\n    12→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    13→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    14→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    15→\n    16→import java.util.Map;\n    17→\n    18→@Path(\"/orders\") // if you already have @ApplicationPath(\"/api\"), change this to just \"/orders\"\n    19→@Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    20→@Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    21→public class OrdersResource {\n    22→\n    23→  @Inject OrderService orderService;\n    24→\n    25→  @POST\n    26→  public Response create(@Valid OrderRequest request) {\n    27→    String id = orderService.place(request); // <-- calls your service\n    28→    // use 202 if you treat it as async, 201 if you consider it created now\n    29→    return Response.accepted(Map.of(\"id\", id)).build();\n    30→  }\n    31→\n    32→  @GET\n    33→  @Path(\"/{id}\")\n    34→  public Response get(@PathParam(\"id\") long id) {\n    35→    // if you already have a repository method, reuse it here\n    36→    // shown minimal for completeness\n    37→    return Response.ok(Map.of(\"id\", id)).build();\n    38→  }\n    39→}\n    40→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PWWVruPQyuEii8v56MeqDs","session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"3e8a3cd4-6650-4b39-a54a-5e5fdd99b974"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KHga9954JzAZXmzZb2e9v9","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.orders.domain;\n     2→\n     3→\n     4→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     5→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n     6→import jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;\n     7→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n     8→\n     9→@ApplicationScoped\n    10→public class OrderRepository {\n    11→\n    12→  @PersistenceContext(unitName = \"ordersPU\")\n    13→  EntityManager em;\n    14→\n    15→  @Transactional\n    16→  public Long save(OrderEntity e){\n    17→    em.persist(e);\n    18→    return e.getId();\n    19→  }\n    20→\n    21→  public OrderEntity find(long id){\n    22→    return em.find(OrderEntity.class, id);\n    23→  }\n    24→}\n    25→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PWWVruPQyuEii8v56MeqDs","session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"9d29174c-0a89-4d4d-8159-4b7ed62eaa78"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UPciWgBqMn7DJ89SMiX7Yt","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.orders.service;\n     2→\n     3→import com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderRequest;\n     4→import com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderEntity;\n     5→import com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderRepository;\n     6→import com.coffeeshop.orders.messaging.OrdersPipeline;\n     7→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     8→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     9→import jakarta.validation.Valid;\n    10→\n    11→@ApplicationScoped\n    12→public class OrderService {\n    13→  @Inject OrderRepository repo;\n    14→  @Inject OrdersPipeline pipeline;\n    15→\n    16→  public String place(@Valid OrderRequest req){\n    17→    var e = new OrderEntity();\n    18→    e.setCustomer(req.customer());\n    19→    e.setItem(req.item());\n    20→    e.setQuantity(req.quantity());\n    21→    // optional: if you added an enum/string status, default it here (PLACED)\n    22→    // e.setStatus(OrderStatus.PLACED);\n    23→    repo.save(e);\n    24→\n    25→    // simple routing: drinks -> barista, everything else -> kitchen\n    26→    if (isDrink(req.item())) {\n    27→      pipeline.publishToBarista(new OrdersPipeline.OrderCommand(\"BARISTA\", e.getId(), req.item(), req.quantity()));\n    28→    } else {\n    29→      pipeline.publishToKitchen(new OrdersPipeline.OrderCommand(\"KITCHEN\", e.getId(), req.item(), req.quantity()));\n    30→    }\n    31→    return String.valueOf(e.getId());\n    32→  }\n    33→\n    34→  private boolean isDrink(String item) {\n    35→    if (item == null) return false;\n    36→    var s = item.toLowerCase();\n    37→    return s.contains(\"coffee\") || s.contains(\"latte\") || s.contains(\"espresso\")\n    38→        || s.contains(\"cappuccino\") || s.contains(\"americano\") || s.contains(\"mocha\")\n    39→        || s.contains(\"tea\");\n    40→  }\n    41→}\n    42→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PWWVruPQyuEii8v56MeqDs","session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"d3ea79ec-f25f-49b0-8a5d-e46168f7a577"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01AxbtbfiVzjPdA728urdDRT","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.orders.messaging;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     5→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n     6→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Incoming;\n     7→\n     8→import com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderStatus;\n     9→import com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderRepository;\n    10→import jakarta.json.bind.Jsonb;\n    11→import jakarta.json.bind.JsonbBuilder;\n    12→import jakarta.json.bind.JsonbConfig;\n    13→import java.util.Locale;\n    14→\n    15→@ApplicationScoped\n    16→public class OrderUpdatesListener {\n    17→\n    18→  private static final Jsonb JSONB = JsonbBuilder.create(new JsonbConfig());\n    19→\n    20→  public static final class OrderUpdate {\n    21→    public Long orderId;\n    22→    public String status;\n    23→    public String from;\n    24→  }\n    25→\n    26→  @Inject OrderRepository repo;\n    27→\n    28→  @Incoming(\"order-updates\")\n    29→  @Transactional\n    30→  public void apply(String payload) {\n    31→    try {\n    32→      if (payload == null) return;\n    33→      String json = payload.trim();\n    34→\n    35→      // Unwrap if the payload is a *stringified* JSON object.\n    36→      int safety = 3;\n    37→      while (safety-- > 0\n    38→          && json.length() >= 2\n    39→          && json.charAt(0) == '\"'\n    40→          && json.charAt(json.length() - 1) == '\"') {\n    41→        json = JSONB.fromJson(json, String.class).trim();\n    42→      }\n    43→\n    44→      OrderUpdate evt = JSONB.fromJson(json, OrderUpdate.class);\n    45→      if (evt == null || evt.status == null || evt.orderId == null) {\n    46→        // dev-friendly: ignore malformed/minimal events instead of killing the stream\n    47→        System.err.println(\"[order-updates] ignored event: \" + json);\n    48→        return;\n    49→      }\n    50→\n    51→      var entity = repo.find(evt.orderId);\n    52→      if (entity == null) return;\n    53→      entity.setStatus(OrderStatus.valueOf(evt.status.toUpperCase(Locale.ROOT)));\n    54→\n    55→    } catch (Exception e) {\n    56→      // DEV: log and continue; do not rethrow or the stream will shut down.\n    57→      System.err.println(\"[order-updates] parse/update error: \" + e + \" payload=\" + payload);\n    58→    }\n    59→  }\n    60→}\n    61→\n    62→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PWWVruPQyuEii8v56MeqDs","session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"83ece570-70b7-4f27-824a-bab449ed67e8"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MRAEcyo7mXKFB13K2UahFZ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.barista.messaging;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import jakarta.json.bind.Jsonb;\n     5→import jakarta.json.bind.JsonbBuilder;\n     6→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Incoming;\n     7→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Outgoing;\n     8→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Message;\n     9→\n    10→import java.util.HashMap;\n    11→import java.util.Map;\n    12→\n    13→@ApplicationScoped\n    14→public class BaristaConsumer {\n    15→\n    16→    private final Jsonb jsonb = JsonbBuilder.create();\n    17→\n    18→    // Consumes commands from orders-service (topic: barista-commands)\n    19→    @Incoming(\"barista\")\n    20→    // Publishes order status updates (topic: order-updates)\n    21→    @Outgoing(\"order-updates\")\n    22→    public Message<String> makeCoffee(String orderJson) {\n    23→        try {\n    24→            System.out.println(\"[barista] received: \" + orderJson);\n    25→            // Parse whatever orders-service sent (JSON String)\n    26→            Map<String, Object> in = jsonb.fromJson(orderJson, Map.class);\n    27→\n    28→            // Carry through orderId if present (original Quarkus did this)\n    29→            Object orderId = in.get(\"orderId\");\n    30→\n    31→            Map<String, Object> out = new HashMap<>();\n    32→            if (orderId != null) {\n    33→                out.put(\"orderId\", orderId);\n    34→            }\n    35→            out.put(\"status\", \"READY\");\n    36→            out.put(\"from\", \"barista\");\n    37→\n    38→            // Produce clean JSON (no backslashes)\n    39→            return Message.of(jsonb.toJson(out));\n    40→\n    41→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    42→            System.err.println(\"[barista] parse/update error: \" + e + \" payload=\" + orderJson);\n    43→            // Let the framework nack and surface the error rather than emitting malformed JSON\n    44→            throw e;\n    45→        }\n    46→    }\n    47→}\n    48→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PWWVruPQyuEii8v56MeqDs","session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"96332831-292b-4124-9b28-00e0f1e139fc"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01X4bmXF2oT1L18DqLL3DEwv","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.kitchen.messaging;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Incoming;\n     5→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Outgoing;\n     6→\n     7→import jakarta.json.Json;\n     8→import jakarta.json.JsonObject;\n     9→\n    10→import java.io.StringReader;\n    11→\n    12→@ApplicationScoped\n    13→public class KitchenConsumer {\n    14→\n    15→    @Incoming(\"kitchen\")          // channel that reads topic: kitchen-commands\n    16→    @Outgoing(\"order-updates\")    // channel that writes topic: order-updates\n    17→    public String cookFood(String orderJson) {\n    18→        System.out.println(\"[kitchen] received: \" + orderJson);\n    19→        // Parse the incoming order (so we can carry orderId across)\n    20→        JsonObject in = Json.createReader(new StringReader(orderJson)).readObject();\n    21→\n    22→        // If original event had orderId, propagate it\n    23→        JsonObject out = Json.createObjectBuilder()\n    24→                .add(\"status\", \"READY\")\n    25→                .add(\"from\", \"kitchen\")\n    26→                .add(\"orderId\", in.containsKey(\"orderId\") ? in.getJsonNumber(\"orderId\").longValue() : -1)\n    27→                .build();\n    28→\n    29→        // This returns a real JSON object string: {\"status\":\"READY\",\"from\":\"kitchen\",\"orderId\":...}\n    30→        return out.toString();\n    31→    }\n    32→}\n    33→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PWWVruPQyuEii8v56MeqDs","session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"4b0e3318-82a7-41a4-904c-fcbed8c6b2bb"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_bdrk_01WgHKYc3Xz7ytvZT6PSFjYk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01RT8kwsx4Sim4ocxRxdwe6Y","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__coffee-shop__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output/orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/web/OrdersResource.java","content":"package com.coffeeshop.orders.web;\n\nimport com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderRequest;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderEntity;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderRepository;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.service.OrderService;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.validation.Valid;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.*;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\nimport java.util.Map;\n\n@Path(\"/orders\")\n@Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n@Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\npublic class OrdersResource {\n    @Inject\n    OrderService orderService;\n\n    @Inject\n    OrderRepository repo;\n\n    @POST\n    public Response create(@Valid OrderRequest request) {\n        String id = orderService.place(request);\n        return Response.accepted(Map.of(\"id\", id)).build();\n    }\n\n    @GET\n    @Path(\"/{id}\")\n    public Response get(@PathParam(\"id\") long id) {\n        OrderEntity entity = repo.find(id);\n        if (entity == null) {\n            return Response.status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND).build();\n        }\n        return Response.ok(entity).build();\n    }\n}\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4565,"cache_read_input_tokens":22418,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4565,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2937},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PWWVruPQyuEii8v56MeqDs","session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"941fd69e-b878-41ef-b6cf-860027039f22"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_bdrk_01WgHKYc3Xz7ytvZT6PSFjYk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01LVhhS5eBXfSRNFSMPUk35p","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__coffee-shop__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output/orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/domain/OrderRepository.java","content":"package com.coffeeshop.orders.domain;\n\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\nimport jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class OrderRepository {\n\n    @Inject\n    EntityManager em;\n\n    @Transactional\n    public Long save(OrderEntity e) {\n        em.persist(e);\n        em.flush();\n        return e.getId();\n    }\n\n    public OrderEntity find(long id) {\n        return em.find(OrderEntity.class, id);\n    }\n}\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4565,"cache_read_input_tokens":22418,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4565,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2937},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PWWVruPQyuEii8v56MeqDs","session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"982ced23-9580-49f8-8e3b-a3ef5c5ae63c"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_bdrk_01WgHKYc3Xz7ytvZT6PSFjYk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01B7JoYNcqovQTaVMiTE2KHu","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__coffee-shop__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output/orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/service/OrderService.java","content":"package com.coffeeshop.orders.service;\n\nimport com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderRequest;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderEntity;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderRepository;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.messaging.OrdersPipeline;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\nimport jakarta.validation.Valid;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class OrderService {\n    @Inject\n    OrderRepository repo;\n\n    @Inject\n    OrdersPipeline pipeline;\n\n    @Transactional\n    public String place(@Valid OrderRequest req) {\n        var e = new OrderEntity();\n        e.setCustomer(req.customer());\n        e.setItem(req.item());\n        e.setQuantity(req.quantity());\n        repo.save(e);\n\n        // simple routing: drinks -> barista, everything else -> kitchen\n        if (isDrink(req.item())) {\n            pipeline.publishToBarista(new OrdersPipeline.OrderCommand(\"BARISTA\", e.getId(), req.item(), req.quantity()));\n        } else {\n            pipeline.publishToKitchen(new OrdersPipeline.OrderCommand(\"KITCHEN\", e.getId(), req.item(), req.quantity()));\n        }\n        return String.valueOf(e.getId());\n    }\n\n    private boolean isDrink(String item) {\n        if (item == null) return false;\n        var s = item.toLowerCase();\n        return s.contains(\"coffee\") || s.contains(\"latte\") || s.contains(\"espresso\")\n            || s.contains(\"cappuccino\") || s.contains(\"americano\") || s.contains(\"mocha\")\n            || s.contains(\"tea\");\n    }\n}\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4565,"cache_read_input_tokens":22418,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4565,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2937},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PWWVruPQyuEii8v56MeqDs","session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"04111894-0de6-4e26-a48d-27c58778000a"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_bdrk_01WgHKYc3Xz7ytvZT6PSFjYk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01DKyZnJoKRok3bZgXuEu6nG","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__coffee-shop__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output/orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/messaging/OrderUpdatesListener.java","content":"package com.coffeeshop.orders.messaging;\n\nimport com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderStatus;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderRepository;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Incoming;\n\nimport java.util.Locale;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class OrderUpdatesListener {\n\n    private static final ObjectMapper MAPPER = new ObjectMapper();\n\n    public static final class OrderUpdate {\n        public Long orderId;\n        public String status;\n        public String from;\n    }\n\n    @Inject\n    OrderRepository repo;\n\n    @Incoming(\"order-updates\")\n    @Transactional\n    public void apply(String payload) {\n        try {\n            if (payload == null) return;\n            String json = payload.trim();\n\n            // Unwrap if the payload is a *stringified* JSON object.\n            int safety = 3;\n            while (safety-- > 0\n                && json.length() >= 2\n                && json.charAt(0) == '\"'\n                && json.charAt(json.length() - 1) == '\"') {\n                json = MAPPER.readValue(json, String.class).trim();\n            }\n\n            OrderUpdate evt = MAPPER.readValue(json, OrderUpdate.class);\n            if (evt == null || evt.status == null || evt.orderId == null) {\n                System.err.println(\"[order-updates] ignored event: \" + json);\n                return;\n            }\n\n            var entity = repo.find(evt.orderId);\n            if (entity == null) return;\n            entity.setStatus(OrderStatus.valueOf(evt.status.toUpperCase(Locale.ROOT)));\n\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            System.err.println(\"[order-updates] parse/update error: \" + e + \" payload=\" + payload);\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4565,"cache_read_input_tokens":22418,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4565,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2937},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PWWVruPQyuEii8v56MeqDs","session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"e426add3-c09e-4ec6-9ae8-760776dcc154"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_bdrk_01WgHKYc3Xz7ytvZT6PSFjYk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01FxaTePY1P27pLpKZa68Q1j","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__coffee-shop__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output/barista-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/barista/messaging/BaristaConsumer.java","content":"package com.coffeeshop.barista.messaging;\n\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.core.type.TypeReference;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Incoming;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Outgoing;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Message;\n\nimport java.util.HashMap;\nimport java.util.Map;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class BaristaConsumer {\n\n    private final ObjectMapper mapper = new ObjectMapper();\n\n    @Incoming(\"barista\")\n    @Outgoing(\"order-updates\")\n    public Message<String> makeCoffee(String orderJson) {\n        try {\n            System.out.println(\"[barista] received: \" + orderJson);\n            Map<String, Object> in = mapper.readValue(orderJson, new TypeReference<Map<String, Object>>() {});\n\n            Object orderId = in.get(\"orderId\");\n\n            Map<String, Object> out = new HashMap<>();\n            if (orderId != null) {\n                out.put(\"orderId\", orderId);\n            }\n            out.put(\"status\", \"READY\");\n            out.put(\"from\", \"barista\");\n\n            return Message.of(mapper.writeValueAsString(out));\n\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            System.err.println(\"[barista] parse/update error: \" + e + \" payload=\" + orderJson);\n            throw new RuntimeException(e);\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4565,"cache_read_input_tokens":22418,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4565,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2937},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PWWVruPQyuEii8v56MeqDs","session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"391c870a-8507-4255-8049-f87e93ae3ceb"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_bdrk_01WgHKYc3Xz7ytvZT6PSFjYk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_016pWpRex18VsLuZaMnHFNZv","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__coffee-shop__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output/kitchen-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/kitchen/messaging/KitchenConsumer.java","content":"package com.coffeeshop.kitchen.messaging;\n\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.core.type.TypeReference;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Incoming;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Outgoing;\n\nimport java.util.HashMap;\nimport java.util.Map;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class KitchenConsumer {\n\n    private final ObjectMapper mapper = new ObjectMapper();\n\n    @Incoming(\"kitchen\")\n    @Outgoing(\"order-updates\")\n    public String cookFood(String orderJson) {\n        try {\n            System.out.println(\"[kitchen] received: \" + orderJson);\n            Map<String, Object> in = mapper.readValue(orderJson, new TypeReference<Map<String, Object>>() {});\n\n            Map<String, Object> out = new HashMap<>();\n            out.put(\"status\", \"READY\");\n            out.put(\"from\", \"kitchen\");\n            out.put(\"orderId\", in.containsKey(\"orderId\") ? in.get(\"orderId\") : -1);\n\n            return mapper.writeValueAsString(out);\n\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            System.err.println(\"[kitchen] parse/update error: \" + e + \" payload=\" + orderJson);\n            throw new RuntimeException(e);\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4565,"cache_read_input_tokens":22418,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4565,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2937},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PWWVruPQyuEii8v56MeqDs","session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"96d5348f-2295-4ab5-a3c5-3c904ae7397d"}
