{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Sq2xpLsSniPDdTP7Gt2ASM","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.orders.web;\n     2→\n     3→import com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderRequest;\n     4→import com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderEntity;\n     5→import com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderRepository;\n     6→import com.coffeeshop.orders.service.OrderService;\n     7→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     8→import jakarta.validation.Valid;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.*;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    12→import java.util.Map;\n    13→\n    14→@Path(\"/orders\")\n    15→@Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    16→@Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    17→public class OrdersResource {\n    18→    @Inject\n    19→    OrderService orderService;\n    20→\n    21→    @Inject\n    22→    OrderRepository repo;\n    23→\n    24→    @POST\n    25→    public Response create(@Valid OrderRequest request) {\n    26→        String id = orderService.place(request);\n    27→        return Response.accepted(Map.of(\"id\", id)).build();\n    28→    }\n    29→\n    30→    @GET\n    31→    @Path(\"/{id}\")\n    32→    public Response get(@PathParam(\"id\") long id) {\n    33→        OrderEntity entity = repo.find(id);\n    34→        if (entity == null) {\n    35→            return Response.status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND).build();\n    36→        }\n    37→        return Response.ok(entity).build();\n    38→    }\n    39→}\n    40→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"861a1197-e400-496c-9e85-b183576a9c0a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GzzWmMGmNfaLxCBEuUM1PP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.orders.domain;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     5→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n     6→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n     7→\n     8→@ApplicationScoped\n     9→public class OrderRepository {\n    10→\n    11→    @Inject\n    12→    EntityManager em;\n    13→\n    14→    @Transactional\n    15→    public Long save(OrderEntity e) {\n    16→        em.persist(e);\n    17→        em.flush();\n    18→        return e.getId();\n    19→    }\n    20→\n    21→    public OrderEntity find(long id) {\n    22→        return em.find(OrderEntity.class, id);\n    23→    }\n    24→}\n    25→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"7156ad38-7745-41d3-8d59-30b70b46789c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QzUCvtcAhnPpqjBGLqcsaS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.orders.messaging;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\n     5→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     6→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     7→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Channel;\n     8→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Emitter;\n     9→\n    10→@ApplicationScoped\n    11→public class OrdersPipeline {\n    12→\n    13→    @Inject\n    14→    @Channel(\"barista\")\n    15→    Emitter<String> barista;\n    16→\n    17→    @Inject\n    18→    @Channel(\"kitchen\")\n    19→    Emitter<String> kitchen;\n    20→\n    21→    private static final ObjectMapper MAPPER = new ObjectMapper();\n    22→\n    23→    public void publishToBarista(OrderCommand cmd) {\n    24→        try {\n    25→            System.out.println(\"[orders] sending barista command: \" + cmd);\n    26→            barista.send(MAPPER.writeValueAsString(cmd));\n    27→        } catch (JsonProcessingException e) {\n    28→            throw new RuntimeException(\"Failed to serialize barista command\", e);\n    29→        }\n    30→    }\n    31→\n    32→    public void publishToKitchen(OrderCommand cmd) {\n    33→        try {\n    34→            System.out.println(\"[orders] sending kitchen command: \" + cmd);\n    35→            kitchen.send(MAPPER.writeValueAsString(cmd));\n    36→        } catch (JsonProcessingException e) {\n    37→            throw new RuntimeException(\"Failed to serialize kitchen command\", e);\n    38→        }\n    39→    }\n    40→\n    41→    // simple DTO for messages\n    42→    public record OrderCommand(String target, long orderId, String item, int quantity) {}\n    43→}\n    44→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"98540419-2d5f-4555-9af3-3c85b3238e7e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VHcwPXbt94yKzpbUeDZU74","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.orders.messaging;\n     2→\n     3→import com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderStatus;\n     4→import com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderRepository;\n     5→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\n     6→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     7→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     8→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n     9→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Incoming;\n    10→\n    11→import java.util.Locale;\n    12→\n    13→@ApplicationScoped\n    14→public class OrderUpdatesListener {\n    15→\n    16→    private static final ObjectMapper MAPPER = new ObjectMapper();\n    17→\n    18→    public static final class OrderUpdate {\n    19→        public Long orderId;\n    20→        public String status;\n    21→        public String from;\n    22→    }\n    23→\n    24→    @Inject\n    25→    OrderRepository repo;\n    26→\n    27→    @Incoming(\"order-updates\")\n    28→    @Transactional\n    29→    public void apply(String payload) {\n    30→        try {\n    31→            if (payload == null) return;\n    32→            String json = payload.trim();\n    33→\n    34→            // Unwrap if the payload is a *stringified* JSON object.\n    35→            int safety = 3;\n    36→            while (safety-- > 0\n    37→                && json.length() >= 2\n    38→                && json.charAt(0) == '\"'\n    39→                && json.charAt(json.length() - 1) == '\"') {\n    40→                json = MAPPER.readValue(json, String.class).trim();\n    41→            }\n    42→\n    43→            OrderUpdate evt = MAPPER.readValue(json, OrderUpdate.class);\n    44→            if (evt == null || evt.status == null || evt.orderId == null) {\n    45→                System.err.println(\"[order-updates] ignored event: \" + json);\n    46→                return;\n    47→            }\n    48→\n    49→            var entity = repo.find(evt.orderId);\n    50→            if (entity == null) return;\n    51→            entity.setStatus(OrderStatus.valueOf(evt.status.toUpperCase(Locale.ROOT)));\n    52→\n    53→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    54→            System.err.println(\"[order-updates] parse/update error: \" + e + \" payload=\" + payload);\n    55→        }\n    56→    }\n    57→}\n    58→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"2d541e59-ea82-4652-8dee-fb4d3691b900"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01B4tZVP5v2QdRP6qqEbUsPz","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.orders.service;\n     2→\n     3→import com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderRequest;\n     4→import com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderEntity;\n     5→import com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderRepository;\n     6→import com.coffeeshop.orders.messaging.OrdersPipeline;\n     7→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     8→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     9→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    10→import jakarta.validation.Valid;\n    11→\n    12→@ApplicationScoped\n    13→public class OrderService {\n    14→    @Inject\n    15→    OrderRepository repo;\n    16→\n    17→    @Inject\n    18→    OrdersPipeline pipeline;\n    19→\n    20→    @Transactional\n    21→    public String place(@Valid OrderRequest req) {\n    22→        var e = new OrderEntity();\n    23→        e.setCustomer(req.customer());\n    24→        e.setItem(req.item());\n    25→        e.setQuantity(req.quantity());\n    26→        repo.save(e);\n    27→\n    28→        // simple routing: drinks -> barista, everything else -> kitchen\n    29→        if (isDrink(req.item())) {\n    30→            pipeline.publishToBarista(new OrdersPipeline.OrderCommand(\"BARISTA\", e.getId(), req.item(), req.quantity()));\n    31→        } else {\n    32→            pipeline.publishToKitchen(new OrdersPipeline.OrderCommand(\"KITCHEN\", e.getId(), req.item(), req.quantity()));\n    33→        }\n    34→        return String.valueOf(e.getId());\n    35→    }\n    36→\n    37→    private boolean isDrink(String item) {\n    38→        if (item == null) return false;\n    39→        var s = item.toLowerCase();\n    40→        return s.contains(\"coffee\") || s.contains(\"latte\") || s.contains(\"espresso\")\n    41→            || s.contains(\"cappuccino\") || s.contains(\"americano\") || s.contains(\"mocha\")\n    42→            || s.contains(\"tea\");\n    43→    }\n    44→}\n    45→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"a73bb7b4-ae16-40d9-9fd1-fe017d40fb6b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DYddzmDWnstLZBYfMxdzyc","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.barista.messaging;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.core.type.TypeReference;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\n     5→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     6→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Incoming;\n     7→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Outgoing;\n     8→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Message;\n     9→\n    10→import java.util.HashMap;\n    11→import java.util.Map;\n    12→\n    13→@ApplicationScoped\n    14→public class BaristaConsumer {\n    15→\n    16→    private final ObjectMapper mapper = new ObjectMapper();\n    17→\n    18→    @Incoming(\"barista\")\n    19→    @Outgoing(\"order-updates\")\n    20→    public Message<String> makeCoffee(String orderJson) {\n    21→        try {\n    22→            System.out.println(\"[barista] received: \" + orderJson);\n    23→            Map<String, Object> in = mapper.readValue(orderJson, new TypeReference<Map<String, Object>>() {});\n    24→\n    25→            Object orderId = in.get(\"orderId\");\n    26→\n    27→            Map<String, Object> out = new HashMap<>();\n    28→            if (orderId != null) {\n    29→                out.put(\"orderId\", orderId);\n    30→            }\n    31→            out.put(\"status\", \"READY\");\n    32→            out.put(\"from\", \"barista\");\n    33→\n    34→            return Message.of(mapper.writeValueAsString(out));\n    35→\n    36→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    37→            System.err.println(\"[barista] parse/update error: \" + e + \" payload=\" + orderJson);\n    38→            throw new RuntimeException(e);\n    39→        }\n    40→    }\n    41→}\n    42→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"f54fe5aa-fac2-46e0-ae17-50e7d73b5802"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012aqNpaJas3dCLWVYM3Tysh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.kitchen.messaging;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.core.type.TypeReference;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\n     5→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     6→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Incoming;\n     7→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Outgoing;\n     8→\n     9→import java.util.HashMap;\n    10→import java.util.Map;\n    11→\n    12→@ApplicationScoped\n    13→public class KitchenConsumer {\n    14→\n    15→    private final ObjectMapper mapper = new ObjectMapper();\n    16→\n    17→    @Incoming(\"kitchen\")\n    18→    @Outgoing(\"order-updates\")\n    19→    public String cookFood(String orderJson) {\n    20→        try {\n    21→            System.out.println(\"[kitchen] received: \" + orderJson);\n    22→            Map<String, Object> in = mapper.readValue(orderJson, new TypeReference<Map<String, Object>>() {});\n    23→\n    24→            Map<String, Object> out = new HashMap<>();\n    25→            out.put(\"status\", \"READY\");\n    26→            out.put(\"from\", \"kitchen\");\n    27→            out.put(\"orderId\", in.containsKey(\"orderId\") ? in.get(\"orderId\") : -1);\n    28→\n    29→            return mapper.writeValueAsString(out);\n    30→\n    31→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    32→            System.err.println(\"[kitchen] parse/update error: \" + e + \" payload=\" + orderJson);\n    33→            throw new RuntimeException(e);\n    34→        }\n    35→    }\n    36→}\n    37→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"3faf83c3-4ecb-4924-b05e-b4622f01a733"}
