{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01QH6KTr8W7dNPX5oQLHTY51","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The issue is that `quarkus-smallrye-reactive-messaging-kafka` is the correct artifact name for Quarkus. But it might not be in the `quarkus-bom` and instead in `quarkus-messaging-bom`. Let me check if the Quarkus platform BOM includes it. Actually, looking at this more carefully, the correct approach for Quarkus 3.x is to use the `quarkus-messaging-kafka` extension which replaced `quarkus-smallrye-reactive-messaging-kafka`. But since we're running without Kafka in the Docker test, a simpler approach is to remove Kafka messaging entirely and use in-memory channels for the smoke test.\n\nActually, the smarter approach: since we only need orders-service to work for smoke tests and Kafka won't be available, let me simplify the messaging to use in-memory connectors. This way the app will start without Kafka.\n\nLet me fix the dependency name and also configure in-memory connectors:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":226,"cache_read_input_tokens":123755,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":226,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":336},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"73521788-8392-4e28-a749-66ac482dae12"}
