{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MbemP3iMNZBnTPJLghtEgD","type":"tool_result","content":"2026-03-14 09:52:40,768 ERROR [io.qua.ver.htt.run.QuarkusErrorHandler] (executor-thread-1) HTTP Request to /api/orders failed, error id: 8a84c620-e8ab-46a9-8cd0-3f027f77994f-1: jakarta.validation.UnexpectedTypeException: HV000030: No validator could be found for constraint 'jakarta.validation.constraints.Min' validating type 'java.lang.Integer'. Check configuration for 'create.arg0.quantity'\n\tat org.hibernate.validator.internal.engine.constraintvalidation.ConstraintTree.getExceptionForNullValidator(ConstraintTree.java:116)\n\tat org.hibernate.validator.internal.engine.constraintvalidation.ConstraintTree.getInitializedConstraintValidator(ConstraintTree.java:162)\n\tat org.hibernate.validator.internal.engine.constraintvalidation.SimpleConstraintTree.validateConstraints(SimpleConstraintTree.java:58)\n\tat org.hibernate.validator.internal.engine.constraintvalidation.ConstraintTree.validateConstraints(ConstraintTree.java:75)\n\tat org.hibernate.validator.internal.metadata.core.MetaConstraint.doValidateConstraint(MetaConstraint.java:130)\n\tat org.hibernate.validator.internal.metadata.core.MetaConstraint.validateConstraint(MetaConstraint.java:123)\n\tat org.hibernate.validator.internal.engine.ValidatorImpl.validateMetaConstraint(ValidatorImpl.java:555)\n\tat org.hibernate.validator.internal.engine.ValidatorImpl.validateConstraintsForSingleDefaultGroupElement(ValidatorImpl.java:518)\n\tat org.hibernate.validator.internal.engine.ValidatorImpl.validateConstraintsForDefaultGroup(ValidatorImpl.java:488)\n\tat org.hibernate.validator.internal.engine.ValidatorImpl.validateConstraintsForCurrentGroup(ValidatorImpl.java:450)","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"0839247d-179e-4b7c-b10c-284c26850531"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_014th7ARgd6XtDxG3diKc7dh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now the issue is `@Min` on `int` being seen as `Integer`. The problem is that Quarkus RESTEasy Reactive with Jackson deserializes JSON into the POJO but the validator resolves `int` to `Integer` through boxing and `@Min` validators don't match. The issue is actually in how Quarkus performs method-level validation on the resource parameter.\n\nThe real issue: Quarkus validates the **method parameter** as a whole using `@Valid`, and when it does so with the constructor-level (or parameter-level) validation, `int` becomes `Integer`. The `@Min` annotation has validators for `int`, `long`, `BigDecimal`, etc. but the validator selected depends on type resolution.\n\nLet me fix this by using `@Min` on `Integer` (boxed) type instead of primitive `int`, and also make the validation work correctly by removing `@Valid` from the resource method and instead relying on field-level validation:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":874,"cache_read_input_tokens":130006,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":874,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":343},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"08615d58-cae1-4b0c-97c2-8e4608f4715c"}
