{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0122LfNaUGH3a18sS5FBwfqT","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.common.domain;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.validation.constraints.Min;\n     4→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\n     5→\n     6→public class OrderRequest {\n     7→\n     8→    @NotBlank\n     9→    private String customer;\n    10→\n    11→    @NotBlank\n    12→    private String item;\n    13→\n    14→    @Min(1)\n    15→    private int quantity;\n    16→\n    17→    public OrderRequest() {\n    18→    }\n    19→\n    20→    public OrderRequest(String customer, String item, int quantity) {\n    21→        this.customer = customer;\n    22→        this.item = item;\n    23→        this.quantity = quantity;\n    24→    }\n    25→\n    26→    public String customer() {\n    27→        return customer;\n    28→    }\n    29→\n    30→    public String item() {\n    31→        return item;\n    32→    }\n    33→\n    34→    public int quantity() {\n    35→        return quantity;\n    36→    }\n    37→\n    38→    public String getCustomer() {\n    39→        return customer;\n    40→    }\n    41→\n    42→    public void setCustomer(String customer) {\n    43→        this.customer = customer;\n    44→    }\n    45→\n    46→    public String getItem() {\n    47→        return item;\n    48→    }\n    49→\n    50→    public void setItem(String item) {\n    51→        this.item = item;\n    52→    }\n    53→\n    54→    public int getQuantity() {\n    55→        return quantity;\n    56→    }\n    57→\n    58→    public void setQuantity(int quantity) {\n    59→        this.quantity = quantity;\n    60→    }\n    61→}\n    62→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write