{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01VfhbLuYbDbBdsBBKyPWReG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The problem is that validation is happening at the method parameter level in Quarkus (`create.arg0.quantity`), and at that level the parameter is inspected using reflection where `int` gets boxed to `Integer`. But `@Min` has built-in validators for `int`, `Integer`, `long`, etc. The error message says \"No validator for `Integer`\" which is unusual.\n\nActually wait - looking at the error again: `No validator could be found for constraint 'jakarta.validation.constraints.Min' validating type 'java.lang.Integer'`. This should work since `@Min` supports `Integer`. The issue might be a Quarkus/Hibernate Validator reflection problem with the field resolution.\n\nLet me try a different approach - remove `@Valid` from the REST endpoint and handle validation manually, or better, just put the validation annotations on the getter methods instead:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":933,"cache_read_input_tokens":130880,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":933,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":643},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"421bd81a-7efa-4fcb-9ebe-0ad7310ec32c"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01VfhbLuYbDbBdsBBKyPWReG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01SxUr199dUD6wnrTSK44EZ2","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__coffee-shop__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output/common/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/common/domain/OrderRequest.java","content":"package com.coffeeshop.common.domain;\n\nimport jakarta.validation.constraints.Min;\nimport jakarta.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\n\npublic class OrderRequest {\n\n    private String customer;\n    private String item;\n    private int quantity;\n\n    public OrderRequest() {\n    }\n\n    public OrderRequest(String customer, String item, int quantity) {\n        this.customer = customer;\n        this.item = item;\n        this.quantity = quantity;\n    }\n\n    // Record-style accessors for backward compat\n    public String customer() {\n        return customer;\n    }\n\n    public String item() {\n        return item;\n    }\n\n    public int quantity() {\n        return quantity;\n    }\n\n    @NotBlank\n    public String getCustomer() {\n        return customer;\n    }\n\n    public void setCustomer(String customer) {\n        this.customer = customer;\n    }\n\n    @NotBlank\n    public String getItem() {\n        return item;\n    }\n\n    public void setItem(String item) {\n        this.item = item;\n    }\n\n    @Min(1)\n    public int getQuantity() {\n        return quantity;\n    }\n\n    public void setQuantity(int quantity) {\n        this.quantity = quantity;\n    }\n}\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":933,"cache_read_input_tokens":130880,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":933,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":643},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-