{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Pe9JswdvLB9KEgfkBZzxnv","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.orders.web;\n     2→\n     3→import com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderRequest;\n     4→import com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderEntity;\n     5→import com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderRepository;\n     6→import com.coffeeshop.orders.service.OrderService;\n     7→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     8→import jakarta.validation.Valid;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.*;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    12→import java.util.Map;\n    13→\n    14→@Path(\"/orders\")\n    15→@Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    16→@Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    17→public class OrdersResource {\n    18→    @Inject\n    19→    OrderService orderService;\n    20→\n    21→    @Inject\n    22→    OrderRepository repo;\n    23→\n    24→    @POST\n    25→    public Response create(@Valid OrderRequest request) {\n    26→        String id = orderService.place(request);\n    27→        return Response.accepted(Map.of(\"id\", id)).build();\n    28→    }\n    29→\n    30→    @GET\n    31→    @Path(\"/{id}\")\n    32→    public Response get(@PathParam(\"id\") long id) {\n    33→        OrderEntity entity = repo.find(id);\n    34→        if (entity == null) {\n    35→            return Response.status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND).build();\n    36→        }\n    37→        return Response.ok(entity).build();\n    38→    }\n    39→}\n    40→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"6975a875-01aa-42ca-8b05-5cf4adfa1ac6"}
