{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01L7tm8S5yVTcXQiNLCNTGsg","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.orders.service;\n     2→\n     3→import com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderRequest;\n     4→import com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderEntity;\n     5→import com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderRepository;\n     6→import com.coffeeshop.orders.messaging.OrdersPipeline;\n     7→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     8→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     9→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    10→import jakarta.validation.Valid;\n    11→\n    12→@ApplicationScoped\n    13→public class OrderService {\n    14→    @Inject\n    15→    OrderRepository repo;\n    16→\n    17→    @Inject\n    18→    OrdersPipeline pipeline;\n    19→\n    20→    @Transactional\n    21→    public String place(@Valid OrderRequest req) {\n    22→        var e = new OrderEntity();\n    23→        e.setCustomer(req.customer());\n    24→        e.setItem(req.item());\n    25→        e.setQuantity(req.quantity());\n    26→        repo.save(e);\n    27→\n    28→        // simple routing: drinks -> barista, everything else -> kitchen\n    29→        if (isDrink(req.item())) {\n    30→            pipeline.publishToBarista(new OrdersPipeline.OrderCommand(\"BARISTA\", e.getId(), req.item(), req.quantity()));\n    31→        } else {\n    32→            pipeline.publishToKitchen(new OrdersPipeline.OrderCommand(\"KITCHEN\", e.getId(), req.item(), req.quantity()));\n    33→        }\n    34→        return String.valueOf(e.getId());\n    35→    }\n    36→\n    37→    private boolean isDrink(String item) {\n    38→        if (item == null) return false;\n    39→        var s = item.toLowerCase();\n    40→        return s.contains(\"coffee\") || s.contains(\"latte\") || s.contains(\"espresso\")\n    41→            || s.contains(\"cappuccino\") || s.contains(\"americano\") || s.contains(\"mocha\")\n    42→            || s.contains(\"tea\");\n    43→    }\n    44→}\n    45→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"378fa943-ccc8-4df5-b10b-466501634566"}
