commit transaction.\n\tat com.arjuna.ats.internal.jta.transaction.arjunacore.TransactionImple.commitAndDisassociate(TransactionImple.java:1319)\n\tat com.arjuna.ats.internal.jta.transaction.arjunacore.BaseTransaction.commit(BaseTransaction.java:104)\n\tat io.quarkus.narayana.jta.runtime.NotifyingTransactionManager.commit(NotifyingTransactionManager.java:70)","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"fc523c78-3396-4fc9-83e5-01cad0322af2"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01DbQ28yXs7kHhGJWpjA1r7w","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The error is `RollbackException` during transaction commit. The Kafka emitter is participating in the transaction and when the emitter can't deliver to Kafka, it causes the transaction to roll back. The fix is to either:\n1. Move the Kafka publishing outside the transaction\n2. Use `@Transactional(REQUIRES_NEW)` or no transaction for the publishing  \n\nThe cleanest approach: move the transaction to just the DB save, and do Kafka publishing after:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1417,"cache_read_input_tokens":148099,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1417,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":232},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"e562e8cc-47e7-4f06-8af2-b94d37934800"}
