{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01Um3ZZ9bbnnjQtZLbQQvdz6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The problem is that annotations are on the getters but the `common` module is a plain Java library (no Quarkus extension for validation). In Quarkus, the Hibernate Validator might not be indexing this class from a non-Quarkus module. The common module doesn't have Quarkus build-time annotation processing.\n\nThe fix is to move the validation annotations to the **fields** instead of getters, since Hibernate Validator in Quarkus should discover field-level annotations. But first, let me also consider that the `common` module may need to be added to the Jandex index. Let me try both: annotations on fields + adding `quarkus-jandex` to common module."}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1859,"cache_read_input_tokens":33710,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1859,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":560},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09dd8e6e-4ff1-445a-9c42-b2dfa0ace457","uuid":"3e288f5a-45b3-41b7-b2e5-f0ada19c0bdf"}
